verses.roman:
prabhu kahe,-rāya, tumi ki kārya karile?
īśvare nā dekhi' kene āge ethā āile?

synonyms: prabhu kahe—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu said; rāya—My dear Rāmānanda Rāya; tumi—you; ki kārya—what; karile—have done; īśvare—the Supreme Personality of Godhead; nā dekhi'—without seeing; kene—why; āge—first; ethā—here; āile—you came.
translation: Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu replied, "What have you done, My dear Rāya? Why did you not first see Lord Jagannātha and then come here? Why have you come here first?"
